ReceiveActivity - Class in com.procom.filefly
The FragmentActivity that will launch in response to an ACTION_VIEW intent from the Android Beam API, copy the transferred file into the received subdirectory of the FileFly directory found on the root of the SD Card.
ReceiveActivity() - Constructor for class com.procom.filefly.ReceiveActivity
 
requireNfcEnabled() - Method in class com.procom.filefly.SendFragment
Presents the user with an android.app.AlertDialog that either forces the user to close the app without action if the device does not have NFC hardware, prompts the user to enable the device's NFC adapter with a link to the corresponding Settings menu, or forces the user to either enable the device's NFC adapter or close the app if a filename has already been chosen through the callback method for ChooseFileDialogFragment.
